  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the sons of Ulam were mighty men of valour,.... Men of great fortitude and courage, though their names are not expressed: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "archers; skilful in the use of the bow and arrows, as the Benjaminites formerly were famous for slinging stones: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and had many sons, and sons' sons, an hundred and fifty; so that the posterity of Jonathan, whose genealogy is drawn down from 1 Chronicles 8:34 hither, were very great; and greater still, according to the Vulgate Latin version, in which the number is 150,000 in the edition of Sixtus the fifth, and so in most MSS of that version (s). ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and had many sons, and sons' sons, an hundred and fifty; so that the posterity of Jonathan, whose genealogy is drawn down from ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 8:34",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " hither, were very great; and greater still, according to the Vulgate Latin version, in which the number is 150,000 in the edition of Sixtus the fifth, and so in most MSS of that version (s). ",
            "children": []
